pubmedtk 0.1.0
  • Reference

    Search PubMed with Optional Year Range Filtering

    search_pubmed.Rd

    This function searches the PubMed database for articles matching a given query. It optionally limits the search to a specified range of publication years and ensures that returned PubMed IDs are unique. This function requires the 'rentrez' package.

    search_pubmed(
  x,
  start_year = NULL,
  end_year = NULL,
  retmax = 9999,
  use_pub_years = TRUE
)

    Arguments

    x

    A character string specifying the search query.

    start_year

    (optional) An integer specifying the start year of the publication date range.

    end_year

    (optional) An integer specifying the end year of the publication date range.

    retmax

    An integer specifying the maximum number of records to retrieve (default 9999).

    use_pub_years

    A logical value; if TRUE, the search is filtered by publication years (default TRUE).

    Value

    A numeric vector of unique PubMed IDs.

    Examples

    # Search without year range filtering
search_pubmed("asthma", use_pub_years = FALSE)
